<h3 id="ensemble-metatone---colour-music">Ensemble Metatone - Colour Music</h3>

<p>Interweaving percussive gesture with electronic sound, Colour Music is a selection of works that seek to redefine how music can be made with touch-screen computers. The seven tracks include the results of a formal study of improvisation on three different iPad interfaces and notated compositions for iPad and percussion. This collection of Ensemble Metatone‚Äôs performances on touchscreen interfaces mirrors the formal explorations of percussion instruments initiated by composers such as John Cage in the first half of the 20th Century, an investigation that is made explicit by the group‚Äôs performance of Cage‚Äôs Trio for 7 woodblocks, first on the original blocks, and then on iPads.</p>

<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=2618109821/size=large/bgcol=ffffff/linkcol=0687f5/tracklist=false/artwork=small/transparent=true/" seamless=""><a href="http://charlesmartin.bandcamp.com/album/colour-music">Colour Music by Ensemble Metatone</a></iframe>

<h3 id="ensemble-evolution">Ensemble Evolution</h3>

<p>Ensemble Evolution created ‚ÄúSounds from the Treetops‚Äù in partnership with the Treehotel to celebrate the culture, landscapes, and innovative atmosphere of their unique working environment in Northern Sweden. Each of the six tracks is inspired one of the tree houses at the Treehotel and the works recall all aspects of northern life, from the icy metallic ring of a still day in deep winter to the otherworldly loneliness of a late night walk under the midnight sun.</p>

